main event: Objects were observed at approximately 23,000 feet by the observer which appeared to be like a boomerang.
interesting points: The object was reported to AGIN/2171., A P-40 at 43,000 feet contacted an unidentified object over Volos, Greece., The pilot of the P-40 estimates the speed of the object at 600-700 knots., The Centralis radar station did not track the object., There was no radar contact obtained on the RHAF aircraft during the sighting.
